TITLE: Iraqi Kurdish oil tycoon's home in ruins after Iran strike
SUMMARY: Iranian missiles that struck northern Iraq earlier this week have laid to waste the sprawling mansion belonging to an Iraqi Kurdish oil tycoon near a U.S. consulate complex in the Iraqi city of Irbil

TITLE: Russia-Ukraine war: Key things to know about the conflict
SUMMARY: Fighting is raging again on multiple fronts in Ukraine, with intense combat in the besieged port city of Mariupol — site of some of the war’s greatest suffering

TITLE: Pope releases long-awaited reform of Vatican bureaucracy
SUMMARY: The Vatican has released the document laying out Pope Francis’ long-awaited reform of the Holy See bureaucracy

TITLE: 4 US Marines die in NATO drill when Osprey crashes in Norway
SUMMARY: Authorities say that four U.S. Marines have been killed when their Osprey aircraft crashed in a Norwegian town in the Arctic Circle during a NATO exercise unrelated to Russia's war in Ukraine

TITLE: Ukraine's leader warns war will cost Russia for generations
SUMMARY: Ukraine’s president says Russia is blockading his country’s largest cities to starve them into submission

TITLE: German TV station hires Ukrainian anchor to host news show
SUMMARY: German broadcaster RTL has hired a Ukrainian presenter to host a daily news show for others who have fled their homeland after the Russian invasion

TITLE: East Timor vote highlights young nation's political impasse
SUMMARY: Vote counting is underway in East Timor’s presidential elections with two former fighters for independence, one current and one former president, considered to be the front-runners

TITLE: Afghanistan world's unhappiest country, even before Taliban
SUMMARY: Afghanistan is the unhappiest country in the world — even before the Taliban swept to power last August

TITLE: Minister: Clearing live ordnance in Ukraine will take years
SUMMARY: Ukraine’s interior minister says it will take years to defuse the unexploded ordnance once the Russian invasion is over

TITLE: Africa mostly quiet amid widespread condemnation of Russia
SUMMARY: Amid a worldwide chorus of condemnation against Russia’s war on Ukraine, Africa has remained mostly quiet — a reminder of the Kremlin’s considerable influence over the continent of 1.3 billion people

TITLE: Ukraine's cultural capital no longer distant from the war
SUMMARY: Ukraine’s cultural capital was a city that could feel distant from the war until the missiles struck within walking distance of the cathedrals and cafes downtown

TITLE: Egypt displays recently discovered ancient tombs in Saqqara
SUMMARY: Egypt has put on display recently discovered, well-decorated ancient tombs at a Pharaonic necropolis just outside the capital Cairo

TITLE: Norway's prime minister says 4 US soldiers killed in plane crash in NATO exercise unrelated to Ukraine war
SUMMARY: Norway's prime minister says 4 US soldiers killed in plane crash in NATO exercise unrelated to Ukraine war

TITLE: Russia-Ukraine war: Key things to know about the conflict
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin has praised his country's troops at a huge rally at a Moscow stadium as Russian forces continue to press their attacks on Ukrainian cities with shelling and missiles

TITLE: Russians are blocked at US border, Ukrainians are admitted
SUMMARY: About three dozen would-be asylum seekers from Russia were blocked from entering the U.S. while a group of Ukrainians flashed passports and were escorted across the border

TITLE: Syria's Assad visits UAE, 1st trip to Arab country since war
SUMMARY: The Syrian presidency says President Bashar Assad has travelled to the United Arab Emirates, marking his first visit to an Arab country since Syria’s civil war erupted in 2011

TITLE: Brazil judge bans messaging app Telegram for ignoring ruling
SUMMARY: A justice of Brazil's top court has ordered the messaging app Telegram to be shut down

TITLE: AP PHOTOS: Day 23: A Ukraine of despair, fear, disbelief
SUMMARY: A woman dressed in a dark blue winter coat and black hat presses a white cloth to her mouth as she stands in the street and stares up in disbelief at the blown-out windows and other damage inflicted by a bomb on a residential building in Kyiv.

TITLE: Bulgaria's ex-PM Borissov freed after corruption probe
SUMMARY: Bulgaria's ex-Prime Minister Boyko Borissov has been freed from custody following an investigation by prosecutors, who failed to come up with enough evidence to press charges

TITLE: Draghi leads push for common EU response to energy crisis
SUMMARY: Italian Premier Mario Draghi has hosted leaders from three fellow Mediterranean countries to push for a common European response to the energy crisis that has been worsened by Russia's war in Ukraine

TITLE: Ethiopian court extends 3-month detention of AP journalist
SUMMARY: An Ethiopian court has extended the three-month detention without charges of journalist Amir Aman Kiyaro to give police 11 more days to interview witnesses, saying after that the state must formally charge him or release him

TITLE: Syria says President Assad has visited United Arab Emirates, his first trip to an Arab country since Syria's war started
SUMMARY: Syria says President Assad has visited United Arab Emirates, his first trip to an Arab country since Syria's war started

TITLE: Spain changes stance, backs Moroccan rule in Western Sahara
SUMMARY: Spain has declared the beginning of “a new stage” in its strained relations with Morocco

TITLE: UN food agency official alarmed by Afghan food, fuel prices
SUMMARY: An official with the U.N. food agency says that with Russia’s war in Ukraine taking an increasing toll on the global economy, the ripples of that conflict will further increase food and fuel prices in the desperately poor Afghanistan

TITLE: UN: 6.5 million people displaced inside Ukraine due to war
SUMMARY: The U.N. migration agency estimates that nearly 6.5 million people have now been displaced inside Ukraine, on top of the 3.2 million refugees who have already fled the country
